						               													<description>This game is based on Phat, a Scottish member of the All Fours family (whose members include Pitch, Pedro, and Don).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Twenty-one tricks are played each hand; the object is to peg points on a Cribbage board for capturing valuable cards. The game end is triggered when someone pegs 180 (or more) points. The hand is completed and the player with the higher score wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is quite simple to teach as it uses standard must-follow trick-taking. To increase balance, one player will pick a trump suit and the other player will pick the rank order (which cards are high or low). What elevates the game is its distribution of card points among the ranks; in particular, trying to avoid giving up the high Phat points for capturing the middle-ranking 9s makes for some interesting and sometimes quite tense decisions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
